The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on relation classification, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses pre-trained language models and neural networks, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves transfer learning, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, as it involves locating target entities, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
